the leader of this group,

00:47:35.350 --> 00:47:37.840
or how do other people as well?

00:47:37.840 --> 00:47:40.227
And then two-- I know
you're saying you first

00:47:40.227 --> 00:47:42.810
got into contact with different
types of people in your record

00:47:42.810 --> 00:47:48.720
store, but I come from a
very white Catholic country,

00:47:48.720 --> 00:47:50.580
and I still feel like
I was always exposed

00:47:50.580 --> 00:47:52.680
to so many different people.

00:47:52.680 --> 00:47:55.950
And I'm just always
on the edge of--

00:47:55.950 --> 00:47:58.950
some people, who are kind of
promoting these hate speeches,

00:47:58.950 --> 00:48:02.340
at the same time, are hiring
people of different races

00:48:02.340 --> 00:48:03.420
and stuff like this.

00:48:03.420 --> 00:48:06.467
So I'm kind of confused as
to how that comes about.

00:48:06.467 --> 00:48:08.550
CHRISTIAN PICCIOLINI: Well,
it's a self-exclusion.

00:48:08.550 --> 00:48:09.660
So even though you may--

00:48:09.660 --> 00:48:11.250
I mean, I went to high
school with people

00:48:11.250 --> 00:48:12.249
of all different colors.

00:48:12.249 --> 00:48:15.630
And even though I had
access to these people,

00:48:15.630 --> 00:48:17.700
I isolated myself from them.

00:48:17.700 --> 00:48:21.990
I didn't want to engage with
them because I was afraid.

00:48:21.990 --> 00:48:25.020
I never admitted it at that
time, but I was afraid.

00:48:25.020 --> 00:48:27.960
And because I was 14
years old when I got in,

00:48:27.960 --> 00:48:29.820
when I was younger,
I never really had

00:48:29.820 --> 00:48:33.870
access to that
kind of diversity.

00:48:33.870 --> 00:48:36.660
And certainly, when I was
14 to the time I was 22,

00:48:36.660 --> 00:48:38.130
I kept myself out of that.

00:48:38.130 --> 00:48:43.530
It was a choice that I made not
to engage with people until,

00:48:43.530 --> 00:48:45.750
because I wanted to
be a good businessman

00:48:45.750 --> 00:48:47.490
or because I was
greedy or whatever,

00:48:47.490 --> 00:48:49.480
I was forced to engage
with these people.

00:48:49.480 --> 00:48:53.490
And then I was like, ah, they
don't fit what's in my head.

00:48:53.490 --> 00:48:56.200
They don't fit
what's in my heart.

00:48:56.200 --> 00:48:59.260
My reality is not real.

00:48:59.260 --> 00:49:02.572
And that's what helped
me build that bridge.

00:49:02.572 --> 00:49:03.780
I forgot your other question.

00:49:03.780 --> 00:49:05.100
What was your other question?

00:49:05.100 --> 00:49:07.020
AUDIENCE: Sorry, I
was talking a lot.

00:49:07.020 --> 00:49:08.400
But my first
question was around,

00:49:08.400 --> 00:49:10.680
when there was acts
of violence, how

00:49:10.680 --> 00:49:13.839
did you describe that to
yourself that that's OK,

00:49:13.839 --> 00:49:15.880
or like anybody in these
types of groups, really?

00:49:15.880 --> 00:49:18.171
CHRISTIAN PICCIOLINI: Yeah,
well, we detached ourselves

00:49:18.171 --> 00:49:19.590
from that too.

00:49:19.590 --> 00:49:24.000
When we hurt somebody, we
weren't hurting a human

00:49:24.000 --> 00:49:25.440
because we had
been so conditioned

00:49:25.440 --> 00:49:29.190
and we conditioned each
other to think and feel

00:49:29.190 --> 00:49:33.210
that the people we were
hurting were almost

00:49:33.210 --> 00:49:37.290
like an inanimate object,
like a parasite or a cockroach

00:49:37.290 --> 00:49:39.690
or a piece of paper that you
could crumple up and throw

00:49:39.690 --> 00:49:40.560
away.

00:49:40.560 --> 00:49:43.380
So that's how we
were able to deal

00:49:43.380 --> 00:49:47.000
with what we were doing is we
completely detached ourselves.

00:49:47.000 --> 00:49:50.850
It became us against the other,
and the other didn't matter.

00:49:50.850 --> 00:49:55.320
All that mattered to
us was us because we

00:49:55.320 --> 00:49:57.840
weren't able to humanize
them because we never

00:49:57.840 --> 00:50:00.810
interacted with them.

00:50:00.810 --> 00:50:04.130
It was almost like a
psychological cut-off,

00:50:04.130 --> 00:50:10.500
like a wall that we had built.
And it wasn't until I had those

00:50:10.500 --> 00:50:14.010
connections with people that I
realized I didn't want to hurt

00:50:14.010 --> 00:50:19.220
them anymore, that I considered
them equal or, in many cases,

00:50:19.220 --> 00:50:21.170
even better--

00:50:21.170 --> 00:50:22.604
many cases, better than me.

