separate from our own,

00:51:01.340 --> 00:51:04.490
especially in this world that
we live in here at Google,

00:51:04.490 --> 00:51:08.560
where we're extremely blessed.

00:51:08.560 --> 00:51:11.030
Can you speak a little
bit more about that,

00:51:11.030 --> 00:51:15.000
especially because it's
likely that all of us

00:51:15.000 --> 00:51:20.655
have an unconscious bias towards
some different even individual.

00:51:20.655 --> 00:51:22.300
CHRISTIAN PICCIOLINI: Sure.

00:51:22.300 --> 00:51:23.695
Yeah, thank you for that.

00:51:23.695 --> 00:51:24.820
It's good to see you again.

00:51:27.810 --> 00:51:29.490
There are two
different realities,

00:51:29.490 --> 00:51:32.010
and I think maybe
November after November,

00:51:32.010 --> 00:51:35.380
we started to realize
that, that there

00:51:35.380 --> 00:51:39.160
are these two sometimes very
separate tracks with not

00:51:39.160 --> 00:51:43.340
a whole lot of bridges
that cross over,

00:51:43.340 --> 00:51:46.130
and we tend to stay
in our comfort zones,

00:51:46.130 --> 00:51:49.400
in our bubbles or
our silos and not

00:51:49.400 --> 00:51:52.760
really cross over because
it makes us uncomfortable.

00:51:52.760 --> 00:51:56.430
Know that, when we hear them
and think, it's ridiculous.

00:51:56.430 --> 00:51:58.550
How can somebody think that?

00:51:58.550 --> 00:52:00.980
They also think that about us.

00:52:00.980 --> 00:52:02.180
Those are the two realities.

00:52:02.180 --> 00:52:06.110
They think, how can
somebody want diversity?

00:52:06.110 --> 00:52:08.210
That's white genocide.

00:52:08.210 --> 00:52:11.829
The more people you allow
in that are not white,

00:52:11.829 --> 00:52:12.870
the white people go away.

00:52:12.870 --> 00:52:14.420
I mean, it's ridiculous, right?

00:52:14.420 --> 00:52:17.600
But there are two very
distinct realities,

00:52:17.600 --> 00:52:18.770
and we really need to--

00:52:18.770 --> 00:52:21.710
if we ever hope to
eliminate some of this

00:52:21.710 --> 00:52:25.480
or to change
peoples perspective,

00:52:25.480 --> 00:52:27.230
we have to be willing
to build that bridge

00:52:27.230 --> 00:52:30.290
and have very, very
uncomfortable discussions

00:52:30.290 --> 00:52:31.980
with them.

00:52:31.980 --> 00:52:33.860
And sometimes there
people that we love

00:52:33.860 --> 00:52:35.960
and we think we
understand, but when

00:52:35.960 --> 00:52:38.810
we hear something like that,
we think, who is that person?

00:52:38.810 --> 00:52:40.490
I don't know that person.

00:52:40.490 --> 00:52:43.100
Well, that person's
the same person.

00:52:43.100 --> 00:52:47.710
They've just had something
appear in their path

00:52:47.710 --> 00:52:50.305
that changed their direction
at some point-- that pothole.

00:52:52.950 --> 00:52:55.174
Just listen, I think,
more than you speak.

00:52:55.174 --> 00:52:57.090
People don't necessarily
like to be talked to.

00:52:57.090 --> 00:52:58.006
They like to be heard.

00:52:58.006 --> 00:53:03.830
So listen, but also
hold people accountable.

00:53:03.830 --> 00:53:05.460
It's important to
do that, right?

00:53:05.460 --> 00:53:11.480
If you hear something that you
know is not right or an action

00:53:11.480 --> 00:53:13.970
that you clearly know is
hurting somebody else, including

00:53:13.970 --> 00:53:16.730
that person, hold that
person accountable,

00:53:16.730 --> 00:53:19.430
but also listen because that
will give you the clues on how

00:53:19.430 --> 00:53:21.646
to build that bridge.

00:53:21.646 --> 00:53:23.032
Yes?

00:53:23.032 --> 00:53:25.360
AUDIENCE: Hi, thank you
