to be there for young people

00:53:55.060 --> 00:53:56.950
as early as possible
from the day they're

00:53:56.950 --> 00:54:00.430
born to not only
teach them empathy,

00:54:00.430 --> 00:54:02.140
but to provide them
with opportunity

00:54:02.140 --> 00:54:04.450
and to amplify their
passions, right?

00:54:04.450 --> 00:54:07.284
I just said young people
don't like to be talked to.

00:54:07.284 --> 00:54:08.200
They like to be heard.

00:54:08.200 --> 00:54:10.109
We need to listen
to young people.

00:54:10.109 --> 00:54:11.650
They have something
important to say.

00:54:11.650 --> 00:54:12.820
They're passionate.

00:54:12.820 --> 00:54:15.730
Their ideas may not
be completely formed.

00:54:15.730 --> 00:54:19.090
They may not have the experience
that maybe some of us have,

00:54:19.090 --> 00:54:21.262
but we need to be there
to amplify their passions,

00:54:21.262 --> 00:54:23.470
to really listen to them
because I could to tell you,

00:54:23.470 --> 00:54:24.940
if I was 14 years
old, and somebody

00:54:24.940 --> 00:54:26.390
would have came
up to me and said,

00:54:26.390 --> 00:54:28.780
hey, you're a really
good artist or you're

00:54:28.780 --> 00:54:30.199
pretty good baseball player.

00:54:30.199 --> 00:54:31.990
Let's find a way for
you to do those things

00:54:31.990 --> 00:54:33.580
that you love to do.

00:54:33.580 --> 00:54:34.960
I would have gone that way.

00:54:34.960 --> 00:54:37.610
I mean, I wasn't
aspiring to be a hater.

00:54:37.610 --> 00:54:41.077
I came from a family that
was the victim of racism when

00:54:41.077 --> 00:54:42.160
they came to this country.

00:54:42.160 --> 00:54:43.940
They were the
victims of prejudice.

00:54:43.940 --> 00:54:45.790
It wasn't a part
of my upbringing.

00:54:45.790 --> 00:54:47.410
I didn't even know
what racism was.

00:54:49.960 --> 00:54:53.440
Let me just use kind of
a theory that I have.

00:54:53.440 --> 00:54:56.350
I think that we should feed
young people, from the day

00:54:56.350 --> 00:54:58.212
